GeneralMessage

Type: object

Message containing all possible objects, without JSON content links

root jobs

Jobs

Type: array

List of directly contained Jobs.

 No Additional Items

Each item of this array must be:

root jobs jobs items

  • RawMxProcessing
  • RawMxExperiment
root jobs jobs items anyOf RawMxProcessing

RawMxProcessing

Type: object

Crystallography Processing calculation,

root jobs jobs items anyOf MxlimsObject version

Version

Type: const

MXLIMS version for current model

Specific value: "0.5.0"

root jobs jobs items anyOf MxlimsObject mxlimsType

Mxlims Type

Type: string

Type of MXLIMS object.

root jobs jobs items anyOf MxlimsObject uuid

Uuid

Type: stringFormat: uuid

Permanent unique identifier string

root jobs jobs items anyOf MxlimsObject namespacedExtensions

Namespaced Extensions

Type: array

List of extensions to metadata, each defined in a NamespacedExtension schema

 No Additional Items

Each item of this array must be:

root jobs jobs items anyOf MxlimsObject namespacedExtensions Namespaced Extension

Namespaced Extension

Type: object

JSON schema for extending MxlimsData. To be subclassed

root jobs jobs items anyOf MxlimsObject namespacedExtensions Namespaced Extension namespace

Namespace

Type: string

Namespace string defining 'owner' of the namespace, e.g. 'ESRF, 'GPhL

root jobs jobs items anyOf MxlimsObject extensions

Extensions

Type: object

Keyword-value dictionary string:Any of extensions. Use is accepted but discouraged

root jobs jobs items anyOf Job startTime

Start Time

Type: stringFormat: date-time

Actual starting time for job or calculation,

root jobs jobs items anyOf Job endTime

End Time

Type: stringFormat: date-time

Actual finishing time for job or calculation,

root jobs jobs items anyOf Job jobStatus

JobStatus

Type: enum (of string)

Status of job - enumerated,

Must be one of:

  • "Template"
  • "Ready"
  • "Running"
  • "Completed"
  • "Failed"
  • "Aborted"

Examples:

"Template"

"Ready"

"Running"

"Completed"

"Failed"

"Aborted"

root jobs jobs items anyOf Job sampleId

Sample Id

Type: stringFormat: uuid

String UUID of the PreparedSample that applies to this Job

root jobs jobs items anyOf Job logisticalSampleId

Logistical Sample Id

Type: stringFormat: uuid

String UUID of LogisticalSample relevant to this Job.

root jobs jobs items anyOf Job startedFromId

Started From Id

Type: stringFormat: uuid

String UUID of the Job from which this Job was started.

root jobs jobs items anyOf Job inputDataIds

Input Data Ids

Type: array of string

String UUID of input Datasets for this Job. For pure Database implementations this field is replaced bu JobInputLinks.

 No Additional Items

Each item of this array must be:

root jobs jobs items anyOf Job inputDataIds inputDataIds items
Type: stringFormat: uuid

root jobs jobs items anyOf Job referenceDataIds

Reference Data Ids

Type: array of string

String UUID of reference Datasets for this Job. For pure Database implementations this field is replaced bu JobInputLinks.

 No Additional Items

Each item of this array must be:

root jobs jobs items anyOf Job referenceDataIds referenceDataIds items
Type: stringFormat: uuid

root jobs jobs items anyOf Job templateDataIds

Template Data Ids

Type: array of string

String UUID of template Datasets for this Job. For pure Database implementations this field is replaced bu JobInputLinks.

 No Additional Items

Each item of this array must be:

root jobs jobs items anyOf Job templateDataIds templateDataIds items
Type: stringFormat: uuid

root jobs jobs items anyOf RawMxProcessing crystalForm

CrystalForm

Type: object

Crystal form, with unit cell and space group, to use for processing

  • Option 1
  • Option 2
root jobs jobs items anyOf RawMxProcessing crystalForm anyOf item 0
Type: object

The following properties are required:

  • spaceGroupName
root jobs jobs items anyOf RawMxProcessing crystalForm anyOf item 1
Type: object

The following properties are required:

  • unitCell

root jobs jobs items anyOf RawMxProcessing crystalForm unitCell

UnitCell

Type: object

Unit cell for Crystal form.

root jobs jobs items anyOf RawMxProcessing crystalForm unitCell a

A

Type: number

A axis length (A)

Value must be greater or equal to 0.0

root jobs jobs items anyOf RawMxProcessing crystalForm unitCell b

B

Type: number

B axis length (A)

Value must be greater or equal to 0.0

root jobs jobs items anyOf RawMxProcessing crystalForm unitCell c

C

Type: number

C axis length (A)

Value must be greater or equal to 0.0

root jobs jobs items anyOf RawMxProcessing crystalForm unitCell alpha

Alpha

Type: number

alpha angle (degree)

Value must be greater or equal to 0.0

root jobs jobs items anyOf RawMxProcessing crystalForm unitCell beta

Beta

Type: number

beta angle (degree)

Value must be greater or equal to 0.0

root jobs jobs items anyOf RawMxProcessing crystalForm unitCell gamma

Gamma

Type: number

gamma angle (degree)

Value must be greater or equal to 0.0

root jobs jobs items anyOf RawMxProcessing crystalForm spaceGroupName

Space Group Name

Type: enum (of string)

Name of expected space group, for processing. Names may include alternative settings. Matches mmCIF item symmetry.spacegroupnameH-M (https://mmcif.wwpdb.org/dictionaries/mmcifpdbxv50.dic/Items/symmetry.spacegroupname_H-M.html).

root datasets datasets items anyOf RawCollectionSweep scans Scan

Scan

Type: object

Subdivision of CollectionSweep.

The Scan describes a continuously acquired set of images that forms a subset of the
CollectionSweep of which they form part. The ordinal gives the acquisition order of
sweeps across an entire multi-sweep experiment; this allows you to describe
out-of-order acquisition and interleaving.

root logisticalSamples logisticalSamples items anyOf RawPlate plateType dropMapping
Type: string

<p>The sender's numbering of the sub-wells. This can be used by the receiver to map the sender's well numbering onto their own.<p><p>It is an error if the sender and receiver disagree on the basic geometry (e.g., three drops across the top with a reservoir underneath). However, they can disagree on the drop order; this property is intended to help overcome such disagreements.</p>
Examples:

"123,RRR"

"23,1R"
